text: Cyclone Higgins, D.D. is a 1918 silent American comedy-drama film, directed by Christy Cabanne. It stars Francis X. Bushman, Beverly Bayne, and Baby Ivy Ward, and was released on May 13, 1918. ==Cast list== * Francis X. Bushman as Cyrus "Cyclone" Higgins, D.D. * Beverly Bayne as Sally Phillips * Baby Ivy Ward as Dorothea * Charles Fang as Johnathon Moses Chi Wu Lung * John Prescott as Jasper Stone * Helen Dunbar as Mary Higgins * Eugene Borden as Owen Chase * Sue Balfour as The Widow Pryor * Pop Kennard as Old Settler * Robert Carson as Sheriff ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:Films directed by Christy Cabanne Category:Metro Pictures films Category:American comedy-drama films Category:American silent feature films Category:American films Category:American black-and-white films
title: Cyclone Higgins, D.D.
